1
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:22,519
There's no need.

2
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:24,359
He doesn't need to—with those injuries.

3
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:26,079
There'll be plenty of use for him later.

4
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:27,319
Hurry back to the bridal chamber!

5
00:02:28,200 --> 00:02:28,919
Go, go!

6
00:02:39,480 --> 00:02:40,119
Wait.

7
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:44,439
Forgive me.

8
00:02:51,680 --> 00:02:52,599
I've lived alone so long—

9
00:02:52,600 --> 00:02:54,159
I keep forgetting there's a man in the house.

10
00:02:59,080 --> 00:02:59,799
Come in.

11
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:13,079
Let me help you.

12
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:14,079
No need.

13
00:03:16,200 --> 00:03:17,239
I can do it myself.

14
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:18,559
Do what yourself?

15
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:20,279
You're really something.

16
00:03:20,480 --> 00:03:22,319
Is it so hard to let someone help apply medicine?

17
00:03:22,920 --> 00:03:24,759
With these wounds flaring up again and again—

18
00:03:25,600 --> 00:03:26,879
how much silver does it take to treat,

19
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:28,039
how much suffering?

20
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,479
Men and women should not touch freely.

21
00:03:33,680 --> 00:03:35,399
What do you mean, 'too close'?

22
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:37,919
When Song Yan came picking a fight,

23
00:03:43,320 --> 00:03:44,079
didn't we already...?

24
00:03:46,760 --> 00:03:49,199
That was not the same kind of touching.

25
00:03:52,040 --> 00:03:54,439
Then carrying you back from the snow—

26
00:03:54,440 --> 00:03:55,439
does that count?

27
00:03:59,240 --> 00:03:59,559
I suppose.

28
00:04:00,480 --> 00:04:01,479
Then that's fine.

29
00:04:07,240 --> 00:04:08,079
Don't worry.

30
00:04:08,720 --> 00:04:10,039
I have no improper intentions toward you.

31
00:04:10,480 --> 00:04:11,679
With all these wounds,

32
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:14,199
even if I did, it wouldn't matter.

33
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,399
Fan Changyu—

34
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:24,359
listen to yourself.

35
00:04:30,160 --> 00:04:31,639
This medicine—

36
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:33,599
no need to use too much.

37
00:04:35,440 --> 00:04:36,239
Too much—

38
00:04:37,960 --> 00:04:40,159
I use this much for Uncle Zhao.

39
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:45,479
You changed the dressing?

40
00:04:45,480 --> 00:04:46,519
I didn't know.

41
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:48,279
Never mind.

42
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:50,279
Just bandage it for me.

43
00:04:59,160 --> 00:05:00,239
These wounds—

44
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:02,679
all from escort work.

45
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:07,599
When I helped you change clothes earlier, I didn't notice.

46
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:08,919
It's fine.

47
00:05:10,240 --> 00:05:12,999
I didn't want you to see—afraid you'd be alarmed.

48
00:05:17,080 --> 00:05:17,919
Bear with me.

49
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:18,879
I'll wrap it up soon.

50
00:05:44,080 --> 00:05:46,239
Other guards rely on skill.

51
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:49,279
You rely on sheer tenacity.

52
00:05:53,920 --> 00:05:55,399
Don't be so reckless in the future.

53
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:56,999
At worst,

54
00:05:57,960 --> 00:05:59,039
I'll work harder—

55
00:06:00,560 --> 00:06:01,959
slaughter a few more pigs to keep you fed.

56
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:24,679
I'll go sleep downstairs with Ning'er.

57
00:06:25,840 --> 00:06:26,679
No need.

58
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:27,879
I'll sleep

59
00:06:29,160 --> 00:06:30,279
in the main hall downstairs.

60
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:33,319
That works too.

61
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:36,519
Let me bring you a basin of water.

62
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:37,759
You can clean yourself up.

63
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:44,199
I'll take your wedding robe downstairs.

64
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:08,039
Why are you hiding something like this?

65
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:12,159
That's not mine—

66
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:14,519
I thought you were resting your injuries.

67
00:07:14,640 --> 00:07:16,079
I had no idea.

68
00:07:18,200 --> 00:07:19,799
I'll let it go this time.

69
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:21,279
I'll throw this filth away for you.

70
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:22,399
No more looking at this.

71
00:07:30,080 --> 00:07:31,119
So embarrassing.

72
00:07:38,080 --> 00:07:38,919
What is it?

73
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,079
Come back, come back!

74
00:07:42,880 --> 00:07:44,679
Be careful—someone might see.

75
00:07:51,560 --> 00:07:52,839
She's coming down, she's coming down.

76
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:26,719
See?

77
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:28,159
I was right.

78
00:08:28,520 --> 00:08:31,359
On their wedding night and they sleep apart.

79
00:08:31,840 --> 00:08:34,439
This girl's marriage must be a sham.

80
00:08:35,200 --> 00:08:35,879
Wife—

81
00:08:36,200 --> 00:08:37,519
you're so clever.

82
00:08:37,919 --> 00:08:39,319
That wretched girl

83
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:41,559
just wants to deceive the government

84
00:08:41,560 --> 00:08:43,158
and hold onto the house by herself.

85
00:08:43,799 --> 00:08:44,919
Look more closely inside.

86
00:08:45,800 --> 00:08:47,639
I am looking closely.

87
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:50,919
I told you to look inside.

88
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:52,039
Who told you to look at that?

89
00:08:58,120 --> 00:08:59,559
Go look over there.

90
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:13,719
Wife, something's off—

91
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:16,119
she just took in water and went back to the room.

92
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:17,559
This doesn't look like separate bedrooms.

93
00:09:17,800 --> 00:09:19,719
Don't panic—let's watch a while longer.

94
00:09:20,560 --> 00:09:21,239
What is it?

95
00:09:25,480 --> 00:09:27,599
My uncle and aunt are eavesdropping outside.

96
00:09:28,640 --> 00:09:30,159
They probably suspect

97
00:09:30,360 --> 00:09:32,119
the marriage is a sham.

98
00:09:39,720 --> 00:09:40,559
Come over here.

99
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:49,479
Can I stay here for a bit

100
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:51,759
and slip upstairs later?

101
00:09:53,040 --> 00:09:54,199
Sleep here tonight.

102
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:58,319
If you leave,

103
00:09:58,960 --> 00:10:00,279
outsiders will become suspicious.

104
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:02,679
Go close the windows.

105
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:14,039
What do you mean?

106
00:10:14,440 --> 00:10:15,919
All the windows are shut.

107
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:17,359
Impossible—

108
00:10:17,960 --> 00:10:19,439
in just that short a time,

109
00:10:20,080 --> 00:10:21,479
that wretched girl managed to spot them.

110
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:23,359
A live-in husband who actually responds to her—

111
00:10:23,880 --> 00:10:24,959
something must be off.

112
00:10:33,920 --> 00:10:34,799
Hand me the candle.

113
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:43,319
Come sit over here.

114
00:11:00,880 --> 00:11:01,679
Turn around.

115
00:11:10,520 --> 00:11:11,479
Closer.

116
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:22,319
Oh—they're going to the bridal chamber!

117
00:11:22,520 --> 00:11:24,199
Right here in the main hall?

118
00:11:24,480 --> 00:11:25,559
Going to the bridal chamber!

119
00:11:30,280 --> 00:11:32,999
Your clothes are soaked through with sweat.

120
00:11:33,400 --> 00:11:34,359
Would you like to change?

121
00:11:42,920 --> 00:11:44,079
Take off my outer robe.

122
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:46,039
Help me lie down.

123
00:12:57,680 --> 00:12:58,319
Don't move.

124
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:03,879
Wife—look!

125
00:13:04,040 --> 00:13:05,639
This is exactly like the book described.

126
00:13:06,680 --> 00:13:07,839
Still watching?

127
00:13:09,720 --> 00:13:11,639
That shameless girl—

128
00:13:47,520 --> 00:13:48,759
blow out the candle.

129
00:13:55,120 --> 00:13:56,839
Wife, the lamp is out.

130
00:13:56,920 --> 00:13:57,719
Nothing to see.

131
00:13:58,080 --> 00:13:58,959
Let's go.

132
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:00,279
Wait—

133
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:02,479
I still feel

134
00:14:03,160 --> 00:14:04,439
something isn't right.

135
00:14:06,800 --> 00:14:07,759
Where are you going?

136
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:09,319
I'll climb back over and look more carefully.

137
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:10,679
Look carefully!

138
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:21,279
Damn wild cat—

139
00:14:21,480 --> 00:14:22,919
stealing my meat again!

140
00:14:24,360 --> 00:14:25,119
That's no cat.

141
00:14:25,640 --> 00:14:26,719
Who's out there?

142
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:35,199
Indeed—such an animal.

143
00:14:35,440 --> 00:14:36,479
How shameless.

144
00:14:36,720 --> 00:14:38,119
Stealing meat in the middle of the night.

145
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:39,399
Next time I catch you,

146
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:40,279
I won't let you off.

147
00:14:45,280 --> 00:14:48,359
Is that girl really consummating the marriage?

148
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,839
Let's hurry and leave—

149
00:14:51,840 --> 00:14:53,639
or we'll be the ones who get buried here.

150
00:14:54,240 --> 00:14:54,839
Quick, quick!

151
00:15:26,960 --> 00:15:27,599
Thank you.

152
00:15:52,480 --> 00:15:53,479
[Advertisement]

153
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:54,519
[Advertisement]

154
00:15:57,560 --> 00:15:58,799
[Advertisement]

155
00:15:59,920 --> 00:16:00,839
[Advertisement]

156
00:16:01,440 --> 00:16:02,439
[Advertisement]

157
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:03,439
[Advertisement]

158
00:16:06,960 --> 00:16:08,399
[Advertisement]

159
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:09,839
[Advertisement]

160
00:16:35,760 --> 00:16:36,719
Just this one piece?

161
00:16:36,720 --> 00:16:37,599
This piece, this piece—

162
00:16:38,120 --> 00:16:38,599
look!

163
00:16:38,840 --> 00:16:39,919
Full weight and measure!

164
00:16:40,040 --> 00:16:40,639
More please!

165
00:16:40,640 --> 00:16:41,159
Sure!

166
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:42,479
Buying braised meat!

167
00:16:42,480 --> 00:16:42,879
This—

168
00:16:42,880 --> 00:16:43,439
pig ear.

169
00:16:44,920 --> 00:16:45,599
One jin.

170
00:16:47,960 --> 00:16:48,639
Thank you!

171
00:16:48,760 --> 00:16:49,679
Just the right fat-to-lean ratio?

172
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:50,559
Perfect.

173
00:16:53,520 --> 00:16:54,399
Thank you, shopkeeper.

174
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:05,959
Shopkeeper, buying meat!

175
00:17:08,680 --> 00:17:09,359
Coming!

176
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:12,318
Two jin, how's that?

177
00:17:12,520 --> 00:17:13,318
That works.

178
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:18,919
Good work.

179
00:17:19,240 --> 00:17:20,239
Sold out already.

180
00:17:20,319 --> 00:17:21,159
Yin Niang.

181
00:17:21,800 --> 00:17:22,479
Ayu.

182
00:17:23,120 --> 00:17:24,639
Just got married and you're already open for business?

183
00:17:25,079 --> 00:17:26,239
Shouldn't you rest at home?

184
00:17:26,960 --> 00:17:28,599
I want to earn more money—

185
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:30,679
get my parents' pig pens back up and running soon.

186
00:17:30,760 --> 00:17:31,799
Naturally I need to work harder.

187
00:17:33,240 --> 00:17:35,919
Besides, there's another mouth to feed at home.

188
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:37,319
Yes, got to work harder.

189
00:17:39,720 --> 00:17:40,839
How did your live-in husband

190
00:17:41,240 --> 00:17:42,639
perform last night?

191
00:17:43,160 --> 00:17:44,759
Fine—can eat and sleep.

192
00:17:44,760 --> 00:17:45,599
His wounds are much better.

193
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:46,999
That's not what I'm asking.

194
00:17:47,160 --> 00:17:49,759
Making children is serious business.

195
00:17:50,320 --> 00:17:52,919
Your live-in husband looks tall and strong.

196
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:54,919
He must be quite capable.

197
00:17:55,440 --> 00:17:56,399
What are you saying?

198
00:17:56,920 --> 00:17:57,879
Listen to yourself—

199
00:17:58,040 --> 00:17:59,159
I don't understand a word.

200
00:17:59,880 --> 00:18:01,439
What do you mean you don't understand? Come along.

201
00:18:14,520 --> 00:18:15,759
What's this about?

202
00:18:16,720 --> 00:18:19,199
They're rounding up drifters from Chongzhou again.

203
00:18:24,040 --> 00:18:25,519
Yin Niang, watch the shop for me.

204
00:18:25,520 --> 00:18:26,559
I'll be right back.

205
00:18:28,280 --> 00:18:29,239
Where are you going?

206
00:18:37,720 --> 00:18:38,599
All handled.

207
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:39,479
Put it away now.

208
00:18:41,080 --> 00:18:41,999
Thank you, Uncle Wang.

209
00:18:43,480 --> 00:18:44,079
Come over here.

210
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:49,879
What is it?

211
00:18:51,640 --> 00:18:52,839
Here's some silver for your trouble.

212
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:54,399
There's no need for silver.

213
00:18:55,160 --> 00:18:56,439
You two are legally married.

214
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:58,239
Everything was done properly.

215
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:00,839
Don't treat me as an outsider.

216
00:19:03,840 --> 00:19:05,159
Then thank you, Uncle Wang.

217
00:19:05,160 --> 00:19:05,679
Of course.

218
00:19:06,120 --> 00:19:06,439
All right.

219
00:19:06,600 --> 00:19:07,519
It's cold—go on home.

220
00:19:23,800 --> 00:19:24,919
Sold! Sold! Sold!

221
00:19:24,920 --> 00:19:25,799
Sold already!

222
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:28,079
How could you sell it?

223
00:19:28,680 --> 00:19:30,039
I had a redeemable pawn ticket.

224
00:19:30,120 --> 00:19:31,439
Look at the ticket more carefully.

225
00:19:32,480 --> 00:19:33,919
It was redeemable, yes,

226
00:19:34,160 --> 00:19:36,319
but there's a clause—

227
00:19:36,760 --> 00:19:38,959
unclaimed after ten days becomes a permanent sale.

228
00:19:39,320 --> 00:19:39,839
Look here—

229
00:19:39,840 --> 00:19:42,199
that's your signature.

230
00:19:43,080 --> 00:19:44,919
Those characters are so tiny no one could read them.

231
00:19:45,800 --> 00:19:47,519
Even if I could see them, I can't read.

232
00:19:48,840 --> 00:19:49,599
Miss Fan,

233
00:19:50,040 --> 00:19:51,559
I can't very well teach you to read

234
00:19:51,560 --> 00:19:53,119
while you pawn things here.

235
00:19:54,480 --> 00:19:55,479
You cheated me.

236
00:19:56,640 --> 00:19:59,119
We followed the contract.

237
00:19:59,720 --> 00:20:00,719
I truly don't understand—

238
00:20:01,040 --> 00:20:02,199
a rough silver hairpin—

239
00:20:02,280 --> 00:20:03,519
that gentleman wanted it too.

240
00:20:03,520 --> 00:20:04,479
You want to redeem it?

241
00:20:04,680 --> 00:20:05,679
What's so special about it?

242
00:20:05,720 --> 00:20:06,599
What gentleman?

243
00:20:06,680 --> 00:20:07,519
Where did he go?

244
00:20:07,520 --> 00:20:08,319
Home.

245
00:20:08,320 --> 00:20:09,639
A customer's information—

246
00:20:09,920 --> 00:20:10,519
speak.

247
00:20:16,800 --> 00:20:17,759
That was the only memento

248
00:20:18,640 --> 00:20:19,959
my parents left me.

249
00:20:23,160 --> 00:20:24,759
He was a young man—

250
00:20:24,760 --> 00:20:26,519
I truly don't know who he is.

251
00:20:27,160 --> 00:20:28,079
How much did you sell it for?

252
00:20:29,880 --> 00:20:30,799
Just twenty taels.

253
00:20:32,600 --> 00:20:34,079
How could you sell it just because someone offered more?

254
00:20:34,080 --> 00:20:35,239
We have the ticket as proof.

255
00:20:37,280 --> 00:20:38,759
We have the pawn ticket.

256
00:20:39,080 --> 00:20:41,639
Even if you took this to the county court,

257
00:20:41,640 --> 00:20:42,839
I'm not afraid.

258
00:21:13,920 --> 00:21:16,119
Changyu, what are you doing here?

259
00:21:18,480 --> 00:21:19,999
What happened? What's wrong?

260
00:21:34,480 --> 00:21:35,039
Changyu.

261
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:54,439
All the candy I'd been hiding was eaten by ants.

262
00:21:55,520 --> 00:21:56,759
Don't cry.

263
00:21:57,160 --> 00:21:58,879
Didn't Father find a way for you?

264
00:22:03,560 --> 00:22:04,839
See—

265
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:07,719
now the ants can't get it.

266
00:22:08,360 --> 00:22:09,959
Father is the best!

267
00:22:10,040 --> 00:22:10,799
Can you

268
00:22:10,800 --> 00:22:13,199
hide this candy for me?

269
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:16,279
You clever little thing.

270
00:22:16,560 --> 00:22:18,399
I knew you had more candy hidden.

271
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:20,399
Don't tell your mother, all right?

272
00:22:20,640 --> 00:22:22,359
Or she'll scold us both.

273
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:23,439
Yes, Father.

274
00:22:25,760 --> 00:22:27,479
Go pluck some grass for Father.

275
00:22:31,400 --> 00:22:32,279
Father gives—

276
00:22:35,720 --> 00:22:36,839
this way,

277
00:22:37,680 --> 00:22:39,079
you won't lose it.

278
00:22:39,400 --> 00:22:40,679
Father is the best!

279
00:22:41,200 --> 00:22:41,879
You—

280
00:22:45,320 --> 00:22:45,959
remember:

281
00:22:46,440 --> 00:22:48,199
every hardship can be overcome.

282
00:22:48,800 --> 00:22:49,799
Let the tears fall,

283
00:22:49,960 --> 00:22:51,199
but keep walking the road.

284
00:22:51,640 --> 00:22:53,679
When the sky falls, a tall person holds it up.

285
00:22:53,960 --> 00:22:56,479
We always eat well and sleep soundly.

286
00:22:56,680 --> 00:22:57,799
Yes, Father.

287
00:22:58,440 --> 00:22:59,159
Good girl.

288
00:23:27,960 --> 00:23:30,959
Thank you, thank you.

289
00:23:31,360 --> 00:23:33,319
See you next time.

290
00:23:33,320 --> 00:23:34,199
Walk carefully.

291
00:23:35,920 --> 00:23:37,079
Carefully, carefully.

292
00:23:37,320 --> 00:23:40,599
Song family's little sister,

293
00:23:40,680 --> 00:23:42,959
so you're moving to the grand mansion in town.

294
00:23:43,320 --> 00:23:45,199
What good fortune!

295
00:23:45,320 --> 00:23:47,039
With the magistrate's favor,

296
00:23:47,200 --> 00:23:49,159
our Scholar Song has done well for himself.

297
00:23:49,480 --> 00:23:50,719
Hoping that next year

298
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:51,959
he passes all three imperial exams

299
00:23:51,960 --> 00:23:54,119
and brings honor to our town.

300
00:23:54,120 --> 00:23:55,519
He'll surely pass.

301
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:58,039
Thank you for the kind words.

302
00:24:00,920 --> 00:24:01,959
Little sister,

303
00:24:02,200 --> 00:24:05,639
now that your Song Yan is about to become

304
00:24:05,640 --> 00:24:08,119
the magistrate's son-in-law,

305
00:24:09,160 --> 00:24:12,719
can you make good on your promise—

306
00:24:12,800 --> 00:24:15,479
get my grandson relieved of his labor duty

307
00:24:15,480 --> 00:24:17,119
and get him a constable post?

308
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:23,319
As for Fan Changyu being a jinx—

309
00:24:23,520 --> 00:24:25,879
I've already spread that around the whole village.

310
00:24:26,320 --> 00:24:27,119
Absurd.

311
00:24:27,440 --> 00:24:28,879
When did I ever ask you to spread that?

312
00:24:30,640 --> 00:24:32,519
No, no—nothing. Nothing.

313
00:24:32,520 --> 00:24:33,399
Nothing at all.

314
00:24:34,360 --> 00:24:35,519
Don't worry.

315
00:24:35,920 --> 00:24:37,279
When the time comes,

316
00:24:37,320 --> 00:24:39,719
I'll have Scholar Song speak to the magistrate.

317
00:24:39,880 --> 00:24:40,839
Understood, understood.

318
00:24:42,160 --> 00:24:43,519
Fan girl—stop right there.

319
00:24:45,360 --> 00:24:46,599
Stand still!

320
00:24:48,400 --> 00:24:50,159
Every hardship can be overcome.

321
00:24:50,800 --> 00:24:53,119
When the sky falls, a tall person holds it up.

322
00:25:00,240 --> 00:25:03,519
We may not meet again as neighbors.

323
00:25:04,280 --> 00:25:05,999
This is our small token of good will.

324
00:25:06,240 --> 00:25:07,479
We hope you'll accept it.

325
00:25:07,880 --> 00:25:10,719
And please return our betrothal letter.

326
00:25:11,760 --> 00:25:12,639
Right—

327
00:25:12,920 --> 00:25:14,919
you've already gotten married now.

328
00:25:14,920 --> 00:25:16,919
Why are you still holding onto their betrothal letter?

329
00:25:21,360 --> 00:25:22,359
This little bit of money—

330
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:26,039
how much do we owe your family?

331
00:25:26,360 --> 00:25:28,719
And when was this—who saw it?

332
00:25:28,800 --> 00:25:29,879
Who even saw it?

333
00:25:30,680 --> 00:25:31,439
Right—

334
00:25:31,680 --> 00:25:33,639
no proof, no one will believe it.

335
00:25:33,840 --> 00:25:36,039
If the Song family really borrowed money from you,

336
00:25:36,080 --> 00:25:38,359
why would they borrow one year and not repay the next?

337
00:25:38,520 --> 00:25:41,119
Who gives for over a decade

338
00:25:41,120 --> 00:25:42,799
without expecting anything in return?

339
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:44,999
It would practically make them living Buddhas.

340
00:25:53,080 --> 00:25:54,079
Fine, fine.

341
00:25:55,600 --> 00:25:57,079
Here's all this money.

342
00:25:57,440 --> 00:25:58,319
Is that enough?

343
00:25:58,320 --> 00:25:59,639
Return our betrothal letter.

344
00:26:06,320 --> 00:26:07,599
Everyone take a look—

345
00:26:08,160 --> 00:26:09,919
this much money isn't enough?

346
00:26:10,200 --> 00:26:11,799
You, Fan girl,

347
00:26:11,800 --> 00:26:13,479
are truly insatiably greedy.

348
00:26:14,120 --> 00:26:15,559
Clouded by greed.

349
00:26:15,840 --> 00:26:17,319
Move aside!

350
00:26:19,480 --> 00:26:21,479
Out of the way!

351
00:26:21,680 --> 00:26:23,079
Bad people picking on big sister!

352
00:26:23,320 --> 00:26:25,319
Brother-in-law stands up for big sister!

353
00:26:31,560 --> 00:26:32,319
Who's this?

354
00:26:32,840 --> 00:26:34,159
That's Changyu's husband.

355
00:26:34,440 --> 00:26:35,439
Him?

356
00:26:35,720 --> 00:26:36,879
He's still a cripple—

357
00:26:39,760 --> 00:26:40,759
your wounds haven't healed yet.

358
00:26:41,160 --> 00:26:42,199
You shouldn't be out like this.

359
00:26:42,320 --> 00:26:43,679
It's fine.

360
00:26:44,400 --> 00:26:45,159
Even injured,

361
00:26:48,120 --> 00:26:49,399
nothing stops me from coming to bring you home.

362
00:26:50,480 --> 00:26:52,479
What business is the Fan family's affair of yours—a live-in husband?

363
00:26:56,240 --> 00:26:59,319
I now carry the Fan name too.

364
00:26:59,840 --> 00:27:01,159
Want the debt repaid?

365
00:27:02,360 --> 00:27:03,519
Fine.

366
00:27:04,040 --> 00:27:04,679
Let's first settle what the Song family owes the Fan family,

367
00:27:05,480 --> 00:27:07,799
then you can move at your leisure.

368
00:27:08,480 --> 00:27:09,639
One coffin: six taels, twenty coins.

369
00:27:11,240 --> 00:27:13,479
Twelve feet of fine cloth: one tael, ten coins.

370
00:27:14,080 --> 00:27:16,279
Thirty baskets of eggs: one tael, fifty coins.

371
00:27:17,160 --> 00:27:19,399
Three years of school fees: nine taels, sixty coins.

372
00:27:20,800 --> 00:27:23,559
Song Yan, that poor scholar,

373
00:27:25,320 --> 00:27:27,199
truly relied on the Fan family's support

374
00:27:27,560 --> 00:27:29,279
to get an education.

375
00:27:29,280 --> 00:27:30,399
And yet—

376
00:27:31,120 --> 00:27:32,119
no sooner did Song Yan pass the provincial exam

377
00:27:32,120 --> 00:27:34,119
than Fan Changyu's parents were barely cold in their graves

378
00:27:34,760 --> 00:27:36,919
before he forced her to break off the engagement.

379
00:27:36,920 --> 00:27:38,959
And the Song family's clothing, food, and daily expenses—

380
00:27:39,760 --> 00:27:41,239
all funded by the Fan household.

381
00:27:41,240 --> 00:27:42,719
Where's his shame?

382
00:27:43,080 --> 00:27:43,879
Exactly.

383
00:27:43,880 --> 00:27:44,759
Exactly.

384
00:27:49,280 --> 00:27:51,439
And what did Uncle record as expenses?

385
00:27:51,640 --> 00:27:54,319
Three years of school fees for that ungrateful wretch—

386
00:27:54,760 --> 00:27:57,359
one year alone is three taels, twenty coins.

387
00:27:57,760 --> 00:28:00,079
Calculate three years—

388
00:28:00,640 --> 00:28:01,719
nine taels, sixty coins.

389
00:28:02,440 --> 00:28:03,559
That's not a small amount.

390
00:28:03,680 --> 00:28:05,479
Plus pork at every festival—

391
00:28:05,760 --> 00:28:07,639
at least twenty portions or more.

392
00:28:07,800 --> 00:28:09,759
That adds up to over two taels.

393
00:28:09,760 --> 00:28:12,319
And two years ago, when Song Yan fell ill,

394
00:28:12,360 --> 00:28:14,439
just the medicine alone cost over one tael.

395
00:28:14,680 --> 00:28:16,079
Fan Er paid for all of it.

396
00:28:16,360 --> 00:28:17,439
He didn't dare let Fan Er's wife

397
00:28:17,440 --> 00:28:18,999
or Changyu know.

398
00:28:19,000 --> 00:28:20,239
The more I talk, the angrier I get.

399
00:28:20,520 --> 00:28:21,919
Even the woman's monthly goods—

400
00:28:27,840 --> 00:28:30,199
four bamboo baskets, thirty bundles of firewood,

401
00:28:30,600 --> 00:28:31,399
five buckets of lamp oil,

402
00:28:31,400 --> 00:28:32,399
three copper basins,

403
00:28:33,280 --> 00:28:34,319
bamboo sleeping mats,

404
00:28:34,400 --> 00:28:35,199
and—

405
00:28:36,280 --> 00:28:36,959
Ning'er, come back.

406
00:28:37,080 --> 00:28:37,839
Don't fall in the ditch.

407
00:28:40,280 --> 00:28:42,839
—and four bundles of monthly cloths.

408
00:28:44,440 --> 00:28:45,279
Monthly cloths?

409
00:28:45,280 --> 00:28:46,239
They borrowed monthly cloths?

410
00:28:46,240 --> 00:28:48,359
And last year at the Dragon Boat Festival,

411
00:28:48,360 --> 00:28:50,039
Old Madam Song came to visit

412
00:28:50,040 --> 00:28:53,119
and stole a braised pig tail while leaving.

413
00:28:55,120 --> 00:28:56,279
Adding it all up,

414
00:28:56,600 --> 00:28:57,519
the Fan family

415
00:28:57,600 --> 00:29:00,199
practically supported the entire Song household.

416
00:29:00,800 --> 00:29:03,199
Matchmaker Kang, speaking up for the Songs—

417
00:29:03,200 --> 00:29:05,399
how big was your cut?

418
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:06,919
Don't talk nonsense—

419
00:29:06,920 --> 00:29:08,679
I got nothing.

420
00:29:08,680 --> 00:29:10,079
I'm the same as everyone here—

421
00:29:10,160 --> 00:29:11,719
I was just passing by.

422
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:14,479
I really was just passing by—

423
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:16,319
I got nothing.

424
00:29:16,840 --> 00:29:18,239
You—a grown man—

425
00:29:18,240 --> 00:29:20,759
talking about women's intimate items.

426
00:29:20,920 --> 00:29:22,759
You're a disgrace to scholars.

427
00:29:23,800 --> 00:29:26,039
Monthly cloths are natural—the very source of motherhood.

428
00:29:26,640 --> 00:29:28,279
What is there to be ashamed of?

429
00:29:28,680 --> 00:29:30,559
You may be ashamed to say it,

430
00:29:30,840 --> 00:29:32,399
but you certainly asked for it often enough—

431
00:29:32,400 --> 00:29:34,639
one bundle at a time,

432
00:29:34,720 --> 00:29:36,079
every other two weeks.

433
00:29:36,280 --> 00:29:38,119
You should see a doctor.

434
00:29:38,120 --> 00:29:39,719
Go see a doctor.

435
00:29:40,440 --> 00:29:41,519
What's it to you?

436
00:29:42,040 --> 00:29:42,799
What are you laughing at?

437
00:29:44,240 --> 00:29:45,359
What's it to you?

438
00:29:45,920 --> 00:29:46,919
What's so funny?

439
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:48,039
What's it to all of you?

440
00:29:48,280 --> 00:29:50,119
Neighbors, please don't say hurtful things.

441
00:29:52,000 --> 00:29:53,719
You're all underestimating the genuine kindness

442
00:29:53,720 --> 00:29:55,079
that Uncle and Aunt Fan showed to me.

443
00:29:55,720 --> 00:29:56,759
They are gone now.

444
00:29:56,760 --> 00:29:57,999
We should not speak ill of the dead.

445
00:29:58,960 --> 00:29:59,519
Ayu,

446
00:30:00,880 --> 00:30:03,079
though you always speak harshly to me,

447
00:30:03,560 --> 00:30:04,639
I don't hold it against you.

448
00:30:06,280 --> 00:30:08,479
I also know your rushed marriage

449
00:30:09,080 --> 00:30:10,479
has something to do with me.

450
00:30:12,320 --> 00:30:13,319
Even so,

451
00:30:13,760 --> 00:30:15,319
from here on we go our separate ways.

452
00:30:16,320 --> 00:30:17,879
But if you ever fall on hard times,

453
00:30:18,640 --> 00:30:20,559
send word to my household.

454
00:30:21,280 --> 00:30:22,679
I will always be your Song Yan.

455
00:30:22,960 --> 00:30:24,159
I—

456
00:30:24,480 --> 00:30:26,159
spare me your kind words.

457
00:30:26,680 --> 00:30:28,159
If not for my sake,

458
00:30:28,720 --> 00:30:30,759
would your mother have treated you so well?

459
00:30:31,880 --> 00:30:33,879
I blame myself for being blind.

460
00:30:33,880 --> 00:30:34,919
What rotten luck—

461
00:30:35,960 --> 00:30:38,439
I fell for a literate, ungrateful wolf.

462
00:30:39,240 --> 00:30:41,039
Pay back the money.

463
00:30:41,920 --> 00:30:45,839
Right, pay it back.

464
00:30:46,360 --> 00:30:47,159
A gentleman parts ways without harsh words.

465
00:30:48,320 --> 00:30:50,199
I'll pay you back.

466
00:30:51,400 --> 00:30:52,439
Rounding off the small change—

467
00:30:54,680 --> 00:30:55,719
thirty taels total.

468
00:30:55,760 --> 00:30:56,559
Count it yourself if you don't believe me.

469
00:30:57,040 --> 00:30:58,799
Give it to her.

470
00:31:04,080 --> 00:31:04,759
We don't have that much money at home.

471
00:31:08,360 --> 00:31:09,959
If you're short,

472
00:31:12,840 --> 00:31:13,879
write a promissory note.

473
00:31:14,200 --> 00:31:15,159
There's no brush and ink here.

474
00:31:16,960 --> 00:31:18,159
When I move to town, I'll write one and send it.

475
00:31:19,000 --> 00:31:20,639
Who needs brush and ink?

476
00:31:20,640 --> 00:31:21,879
Bite your finger,

477
00:31:22,440 --> 00:31:23,839
press your thumbprint.

478
00:31:24,320 --> 00:31:25,519
Right, a thumbprint.

479
00:31:26,320 --> 00:31:29,199
Quick.

480
00:31:29,480 --> 00:31:29,879
Stop—

481
00:31:29,880 --> 00:31:30,959
don't listen to them.

482
00:31:31,080 --> 00:31:32,079
Wait, wait!

483
00:31:34,480 --> 00:31:35,599
Just a few dozen taels—

484
00:31:52,000 --> 00:31:53,319
I'll repay it for him.

485
00:31:53,560 --> 00:31:54,559
Miss Cui—

486
00:31:58,760 --> 00:31:59,959
how could we ask you to come down to a place like this?

487
00:31:59,960 --> 00:32:02,919
Scholar Song is my father's student.

488
00:32:04,200 --> 00:32:06,599
It's only right I help.

489
00:32:06,920 --> 00:32:07,919
A student of the Son of Heaven—

490
00:32:08,120 --> 00:32:09,039
how can he be schemed against

491
00:32:10,760 --> 00:32:12,199
by someone reeking of money?

492
00:32:12,600 --> 00:32:14,399
Some people are born noble.

493
00:32:14,560 --> 00:32:15,919
Like me—

494
00:32:28,840 --> 00:32:31,279
my father named me Qianjin,

495
00:32:31,920 --> 00:32:32,599
meaning a thousand gold,

496
00:32:33,480 --> 00:32:35,679
destined never to lack for silver.

497
00:32:35,840 --> 00:32:37,999
Born to command others.

498
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:39,159
And some are born lowly.

499
00:32:40,240 --> 00:32:43,319
Like you—

500
00:32:43,960 --> 00:32:44,639
orphaned from childhood,

501
00:32:45,560 --> 00:32:47,239
with no one in this world.

502
00:32:47,240 --> 00:32:48,399
This jade may be beautiful,

503
00:32:49,080 --> 00:32:50,439
but it's worth less than gold and silver.

504
00:32:50,760 --> 00:32:52,559
Here's fifty taels.

505
00:32:53,360 --> 00:32:54,559
Pick it up.

506
00:32:55,160 --> 00:32:56,159
All right, Chang Ning—

507
00:33:08,520 --> 00:33:09,319
we don't take what isn't ours.

508
00:33:10,040 --> 00:33:11,199
The betrothal letter has long been placed

509
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:14,399
under the stone at your door.

510
00:33:14,400 --> 00:33:15,279
Mother—

511
00:33:16,560 --> 00:33:17,199
we've been over for a long time.

512
00:33:18,440 --> 00:33:19,559
This extra money is just interest.

513
00:33:21,400 --> 00:33:23,679
After all,

514
00:33:23,960 --> 00:33:25,919
your pride

515
00:33:26,400 --> 00:33:27,519
isn't worth much.

516
00:33:28,080 --> 00:33:31,239
What isn't mine, I won't take.

517
00:33:31,240 --> 00:33:31,919
Besides—

518
00:33:33,480 --> 00:33:34,759
he isn't worth it.

519
00:33:37,520 --> 00:33:39,199
Wait—I'm not done speaking.

520
00:33:39,600 --> 00:33:40,399
Come back here.

521
00:33:40,400 --> 00:33:41,159
So rude. Scholar Song,

522
00:33:41,160 --> 00:33:42,719
come help me.

523
00:33:45,480 --> 00:33:46,359
Whoever picks up those coins can keep them.

524
00:33:46,360 --> 00:33:47,959
This money belongs to whoever wants it.

525
00:34:02,360 --> 00:34:03,519
Sure, sure—come, come.

526
00:34:06,080 --> 00:34:06,839
Finally—

527
00:34:10,639 --> 00:34:11,799
finally found it.

528
00:34:13,760 --> 00:34:14,559
Tear it up.

529
00:34:19,720 --> 00:34:21,638
Ning'er, come home with your brother-in-law.

530
00:34:43,760 --> 00:34:45,319
He's just a provincial licentiate.

531
00:34:45,840 --> 00:34:47,399
In Da Yin, with seventeen prefectures—

532
00:34:47,840 --> 00:34:49,198
how many licentiates are there each year?

533
00:34:49,560 --> 00:34:51,279
Who does Song Yan think he is?

534
00:34:55,240 --> 00:34:56,439
In the future,

535
00:34:56,679 --> 00:34:58,319
just say this kind of thing to me,

536
00:34:59,120 --> 00:35:00,519
not in front of outsiders.

537
00:35:01,080 --> 00:35:01,959
People will laugh.

538
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:03,279
Laugh?

539
00:35:04,760 --> 00:35:05,679
Laugh at what?

540
00:35:06,280 --> 00:35:07,479
They'll laugh at you—

541
00:35:07,720 --> 00:35:09,199
for not even having a licentiate's degree.

542
00:35:14,880 --> 00:35:17,559
I know you're saying this to cheer me up.

543
00:35:19,800 --> 00:35:20,759
Why would I cheer you up?

544
00:35:20,960 --> 00:35:22,119
Never mind a licentiate—

545
00:35:22,520 --> 00:35:23,559
even a palace exam graduate

546
00:35:24,240 --> 00:35:25,519
is nothing special.

547
00:35:28,480 --> 00:35:30,479
You really think highly of yourself.

548
00:35:31,840 --> 00:35:32,119
I—

549
00:35:32,320 --> 00:35:33,559
I see you're smart,

550
00:35:34,120 --> 00:35:35,319
your handwriting is good.

551
00:35:36,040 --> 00:35:38,479
Why not study and take the exams?

552
00:35:38,840 --> 00:35:40,159
If you pass the provincial exam,

553
00:35:40,280 --> 00:35:41,519
you'd get an official post.

554
00:35:42,440 --> 00:35:43,679
My ambitions don't lie in officialdom.

555
00:35:47,120 --> 00:35:48,679
What a pity.

556
00:35:48,960 --> 00:35:51,719
I was counting on you becoming a great official

557
00:35:51,880 --> 00:35:54,319
and finding ways to give that Song fellow trouble.

558
00:35:57,640 --> 00:35:58,159
Fine.

559
00:36:03,360 --> 00:36:03,959
What's wrong?

560
00:36:08,360 --> 00:36:09,759
Actually, what makes me sad

561
00:36:11,160 --> 00:36:12,319
isn't Song Yan.

562
00:36:14,440 --> 00:36:16,359
It's my mother's hairpin—I can't get it back.

563
00:36:29,080 --> 00:36:32,359
The truth is, that hairpin—I let my parents down.

564
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:34,679
I pawned it as a redeemable pawn,

565
00:36:35,240 --> 00:36:37,079
but ran into a dishonest pawnbroker

566
00:36:37,280 --> 00:36:39,119
who sold it to some fool.

567
00:36:39,720 --> 00:36:40,879
That fool

568
00:36:40,960 --> 00:36:42,479
paid twenty taels for it.

569
00:36:42,560 --> 00:36:43,839
Twenty taels.

570
00:36:44,240 --> 00:36:45,639
So much money—

571
00:36:45,960 --> 00:36:47,479
I could never afford that.

572
00:36:49,080 --> 00:36:50,639
Tell me—how can there be someone in the world

573
00:36:50,640 --> 00:36:51,679
who just creates problems for others?

574
00:37:04,160 --> 00:37:05,519
How did this end up with you?

575
00:37:05,960 --> 00:37:06,799
That gentleman—

576
00:37:11,160 --> 00:37:13,079
are you the one who paid twenty taels to redeem it?

577
00:37:15,640 --> 00:37:16,999
You could say that.

578
00:37:21,840 --> 00:37:22,559
You're back.

579
00:37:28,360 --> 00:37:29,039
Wait.

580
00:37:29,760 --> 00:37:30,799
That dishonest pawnbroker cheated you out of twenty taels.

581
00:37:31,680 --> 00:37:33,639
I need to get that money back.

582
00:37:34,560 --> 00:37:35,759
Actually, that gentleman

583
00:37:41,240 --> 00:37:42,719
is the bookshop owner.

584
00:37:43,960 --> 00:37:45,399
He paid twenty taels for the hairpin.

585
00:37:46,520 --> 00:37:48,479
He appreciates my essays,

586
00:37:51,120 --> 00:37:52,519
so when he sent payment for my writing,

587
00:37:52,680 --> 00:37:55,759
he included the hairpin as a bonus.

588
00:37:56,040 --> 00:37:57,319
What a coincidence.

589
00:37:58,080 --> 00:37:58,919
Yes.

590
00:38:00,800 --> 00:38:01,399
Here's the silver.

591
00:38:06,640 --> 00:38:07,439
You sell essays

592
00:38:13,240 --> 00:38:14,279
and earn this much?

593
00:38:15,040 --> 00:38:16,199
Uncle Zhao can vouch for that.

594
00:38:16,560 --> 00:38:18,639
Where is that bookshop?

595
00:38:19,280 --> 00:38:20,359
I want to return the money to the gentleman.

596
00:38:21,200 --> 00:38:22,519
No need.

597
00:38:22,760 --> 00:38:23,359
That gentleman has great wealth.

598
00:38:24,040 --> 00:38:25,439
He doesn't miss twenty taels.

599
00:38:25,960 --> 00:38:27,319
Still, I should thank him.

600
00:38:27,680 --> 00:38:28,999
Of course.

601
00:38:30,880 --> 00:38:31,799
Once my wounds heal,

602
00:38:32,880 --> 00:38:35,159
I'll take you to visit.

603
00:38:35,600 --> 00:38:36,759
All right.

604
00:38:38,560 --> 00:38:39,279
Actually,

605
00:38:42,880 --> 00:38:43,799
you don't need to sell essays to support the household.

606
00:38:44,360 --> 00:38:46,439
I said—

607
00:38:48,560 --> 00:38:49,479
I can raise pigs and keep you.

608
00:38:50,840 --> 00:38:52,039
Mother.

609
00:39:16,560 --> 00:39:17,319
I found the hairpin.

610
00:39:17,680 --> 00:39:18,799
Before,

611
00:39:20,240 --> 00:39:20,999
I was always afraid of doing the wrong thing,

612
00:39:21,840 --> 00:39:23,159
afraid you wouldn't approve of my choices,

613
00:39:24,920 --> 00:39:26,519
afraid you'd be angry.

614
00:39:26,560 --> 00:39:27,599
Now this hairpin

615
00:39:29,160 --> 00:39:30,319
has come back to me by a winding path.

616
00:39:30,480 --> 00:39:31,959
It must be you watching over us from above.

617
00:39:33,600 --> 00:39:35,879
I'm at ease now.

618
00:39:38,760 --> 00:39:40,159
Let me help you.

619
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:57,799
Wait.

620
00:41:40,400 --> 00:41:41,079
Brother An,

621
00:41:41,440 --> 00:41:42,119
I have a chicken leg.

622
00:41:42,120 --> 00:41:42,959
Want some?

623
00:41:44,680 --> 00:41:45,279
I—

624
00:41:47,040 --> 00:41:48,159
I don't eat chicken legs.

625
00:41:48,440 --> 00:41:49,639
I have a big one here.

626
00:41:49,640 --> 00:41:50,679
Look.

627
00:41:52,800 --> 00:41:54,079
This is most improper.

628
00:41:54,360 --> 00:41:56,839
How can one eat meat in such a refined place of learning?

629
00:41:57,520 --> 00:41:58,759
Aren't you afraid the headmaster will scold you?

630
00:42:44,280 --> 00:42:45,239
You clumsy bird—

631
00:42:45,520 --> 00:42:46,999
you always lose your way coming here.

632
00:42:52,720 --> 00:42:53,759
I know, I know.

633
00:42:53,760 --> 00:42:55,439
Wait here a moment.

634
00:42:58,000 --> 00:42:59,879
Your punishment copy is considered complete.

635
00:43:00,080 --> 00:43:00,999
The rest of you may go.

636
00:43:02,840 --> 00:43:03,519
Thank you, Headmaster.

637
00:43:04,240 --> 00:43:06,159
Brother An, thank Headmaster Gongsun.

638
00:43:07,320 --> 00:43:08,999
Thank you, Headmaster Gongsun.

639
00:43:16,160 --> 00:43:18,319
I am currently staying at the Fan family home in Lin'an

640
00:43:19,120 --> 00:43:20,759
to recover from my injuries.

641
00:43:21,040 --> 00:43:21,999
Here are my household papers and travel documents for verification.

642
00:43:29,880 --> 00:43:31,279
Well, you, Xie Jiuheng—

643
00:43:31,880 --> 00:43:33,959
I knew a fellow like you wouldn't die so easily.
